This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) tools and conversational dialogue systems. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves automated judgment models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the method involves training a classifier. It could also be classified under cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it deals with the evaluation of software systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it involves human ratings on dialogues.
